text: The Kengale Koli, or Kangle Koli (Hindi: केंगले कोली) is a clan (Gotra) of the Koli caste found in the Maharashtra state of India. The Kolis of Kengle clan revolted against British rule and Sahukars, or Moneylenders in Deccan in 1872 to 1876 under their chief. == Notable == * Honya Kengle, freedom activist from Maharashtra == References == Category:Koli clans
title: Kengale Koli
